{"id":"bedstead","term":"Bedstead","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Used in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 3:11\">Deut. 3:11</a>, but elsewhere rendered “couch,” “bed.” In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 1:4\">2 Kings 1:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 16:2\">16:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 132:3\">Ps. 132:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Amos 3:12\">Amos 3:12</a>, the divan is meant by this word.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Deuteronomy 3:11","2 Kings 1:4","2 Kings 16:2","Psalms 132:3","Amos 3:12"]}